==> INTRODUCTION
I wrote this game primarily for nostalgic reasons. In the early
eighties during those hours I was supposed to be at school, I
very much enjoyed playing the video games "Centipede", "Spiders",
"Hydra-X", "Galaga" and many others. As I never really found a decent
"Centipede" clone for the Amiga I decided to try programme one on 
myself in 1992. Now just a couple of years later I eventually 
completed "Creepy Crawlies"!

It took so long to complete it as I spent considerable effort on
the graphics. The most colourful graphics are only achieved with
the extra halfbright mode. It then of course took ages to draw all
the objects in hundreds of colours. Another problem was that the 
use of 6 bitmaps seriously slows down a 68000 Amiga. It always was
my intention to write the game in a manner that it would just as
well work on a small Amiga 500 with 1 MB RAM and ancient OS 1.2.


