==> SETUP
Basically you can start the game using the CLI or the workbench from
whatever source you like. Don't be dissapointed if the game takes a few
seconds to start! If the game wants you to insert a disk into drive
df0:, just ignore it. The game will start a few seconds afterwards.

To enjoy all the features I would rather recommend to do the
following:

   - Take an empty (formatted) disk.
   - Remember to "install" it, if you prefer to autoboot the game.
   - ALLWAYS keep the disk write enabled! (Your computer will "hang"
     otherwise when it attempts to write the highscore list).
   - Copy all the files contained in "Creepy.lha" to your disk in 
     drive df0:
        s/startup-sequence
        Creepy Crawlies
        Creepy Crawlies.info
        Creepy Crawlies.readme
        
The advantages of operating the game from a disk are the follwing:

   - The game is equipped with a saveable highscore list which is 
     only written onto a disk in drive df0:. The reason simply is
     that I don't fancy the idea very much that a game writes
     highscore lists onto my harddisk!
   - Once the game is on a disk it can permanently be converted to 
     the full version when you have obtained the necessary codeword
     from me. Your game on the disk will be modified which it will
     only do when it is operated from a disk in drive df0:!
